LogFile.FinalText: Some people claim that men and women speak different languages. If a man who lives with a woman says that he does not want to speak about his problems, the typical woman feels that she is excluded from his world. If the woman tells him that she does not want to speak about the problems, most men think that she does not need to discus the problems. These misunderstandings give rise to disagreements. When such disagreements arise, women and men also react in different ways. New research shows that many women cry when they get upset. In these situations, frightened men choose to fly, and they may feel helpless. As opposed to the crying woman, the angry man uses hard words. In spite of these different reactions, most men and women are able to live peacefully together, and most of us probably agree that we cannot live without eachother.
